       Section 2.4  What You Receive When You Order

       When you  purchase a  copy of  The Blue  Wave Offline Mail Reader, you
       will  receive   a  registration   letter  which  contains  details  on
       converting your  copy of  the mail  reader into  a registered version.
       The registration  letter will  assign you  a unique  user registration
       number based  upon the  name you  supplied  when  you  submitted  your
       registration form.   To  convert your  copy of  the mail reader into a
       fully licensed version, you simply need to enter the registration name
       and number  supplied into the "Setup/Configure Mail Reader" portion of
       the program.   The  next time  you  load  the  mail  reader,  it  will
       recognize you as a registered owner of the software.

       In order  to keep registration costs low, we do not automatically ship
       a disk  containing a  copy of  the software.  Since you already HAVE a
       copy of  the software,  we can  simply provide you with a registration
       number to  activate the software license.  If you would like to insure
       that you  have the  latest version  of the  mail reader, we do offer a
       disk mailing service for and additional $5.00US.

       Sorry, we currently do not offer a printed manual for the mail reader.
       With the  online documentation/help system built into the mail reader,
       we have  found that  most users  do not need or do not want to pay the
       extra cost of providing a printed manual.

       Please be  sure to  keep the  registration letter you receive from us.
       You may  need your  registration number  handy in  the case  of a disk
       failure or  other system  crash.  This registration letter also serves
       as your official software license.

       If  you   lose  or   otherwise  misplace  your  software  registration
       certificate, we  can provide  you with  a replacement  copy.  You must
       send your  request to our mailing address along with a self-addressed,
       STAMPED envelope.  (Users outside of the United States must enclose an
       International  Reply   Coupon,  available   at  your   post   office).
       Replacement registration  codes will  NOT be  given by any other means
